50|$|Xist is {{expressed}} {{from one of}} the X chromosomes in females and serves to inactivate the other X chromosome during X inactivation. Many copies of Xist RNA bind the future inactivated X chromosome. Tsix prevents the accumulation of Xist on the future active female X chromosome to maintain the active <b>euchromatin</b> state of the chosen chromosome.|$|E
